ary. It's good to think about importing `NativeImageSupport` as an existing dependency. I also wonder if, when releasing in a try block, I should set `registered=false`. \\n\\nI think if there’s an assertion error, it might be better to release it after the assertion check. Catching all `Error` includes `AssertionError`, so I need to be careful with the catch clause.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated test for the active dynamic-access class:\n\n- Added `tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/LambdaFactoryTest.java`\n\nThe test exercises:\n\n- `LambdaFactory.register(...)`\n- reflective field access and constructor/method lookup during registration\n- `LambdaFactory.make(...)`, including dispatcher invocation\n- `LambdaFactory.release(...)`, including system class loader lookup and field access\n\nIt also catches Native Image unsupported dynamic class-loading `Error`s using `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)` as required.\n\nPer instruction, I did not run or compile the tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e0402c8787bbe490169fa9e9ee08481a0990dacf9240f2c2a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 584, "output": 908, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22996, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778032275210, "responseId": "resp_0e0402c8787bbe490169fa9e93a28881a0baf15b211b1d163b"}, "toolResults": []}
